reviews.content: I don't like expensive restaurants, I love eating there because I'M with my family the name of my favourte restaurant is Quan cua ngon-huong vi dat mui, It's always busy and it very friendly...., there or always lots of familes

Fresh and delicious crab, sweet meat. The crab weight does not include the rope. Many flavors are processed, my favorite is Tamarind Crab. I eat so much that I become a VIP customer ü§£ The restaurant now only has a branch in Nguyen Thai ‚Ä¶
Delicious food, firm crab meat, firm roe. The price is worth the food. I brought my parents here and they were very satisfied.
Delicious, new, fresh, quality crab. First time experience and will come back when craving ü¶Ä ‚Ä¶

Familiar address for 4-5 years, the crabs here are definitely sweet, true to the slogan "A Million Children Like One", whether eating at the restaurant or having it delivered, I love the pepper crab and spicy bamboo shoot hotpot the most, friendly staff!

On a business trip to Saigon, I stopped by to buy crabs as gifts. The staff carefully packed each crab, clearly labeled each one and printed the logo. Very professional. I also took the opportunity to try the Thai curry crab on the spot ‚Äì the broth was rich and very unique. A memorable experience before going to the airport.

Close to the airport so ordering crab to go is extremely convenient. Every time I go back to my hometown to visit my mother, my family orders crab here to take home. The shop packages the crab very professionally and also gives away delicious sauce.

My company hosted a party for foreign guests and chose this restaurant. Everyone was amazed by the delicious and beautifully presented Vietnamese crab. The staff were enthusiastic and spoke good English. The garlic and Thai curry were great highlights.
